### POST /api/groups/managers/user

This endpoint is used to add a user to the managers group.

#### Request Body

- username (string, required): The username of the user to be added to the managers group.


Example:

``` json
{
    "username": "barry_backend"
}

 ```

#### Response

The response is in JSON format and has a status code of 201 (Created).

#### JSON Schema

``` json
{
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "response": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Interpolated string providing confirmation of the role addition and the update to their perissions."
        }
    }
}

 ```

### Delete User from Delivery Crew Group

The endpoint sends an HTTP DELETE request to remove a user with a specific employee ID from the "delivery-crew" group.

## Request

#### Request Parameters

- `employee_id` (path parameter) : The ID of the employee to be removed from the managers group.


## Response

The response returned has a status code of 200 and a content type of "application/json". Below is the JSON schema for the response:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "response": {
      "type": "string"
    }
  }
}

 ```

### Delete User from Managers Group

