The endpoint allows users to make an HTTP POST request to log in and obtain a token.

### Request Body

_Note: The request body is paramerterized. If your user was created via the_ [<i>Create New User</i>](https://www.postman.com/blackberry-py-dev/workspace/little-lemon-meta-apis-final-terry-brooks-jr/request/20135114-f11c33e2-c4f9-4a73-967e-876ee228af4e?action=share&source=copy-link&creator=20135114&ctx=documentation) _request in Postman, these keys will be replaced with the correct vakuyeds_

- username (string): The username of the user.

- password (string): The password of the user.


### Response

The response of the request is a JSON object with a status code of 200 and a content type of application/json. The response schema for the 200 status code is as follows:

``` json
{
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "auth_token": {
            "type": "string"
        }
    }
}

 ```

